SIMPLE: domineer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Domineer
<hw>Dom`i*neer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Domineered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Domineering</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[F. <ets>dominer</ets>, L. <ets>dominari</ets>: cf. OD.
<ets>domineren</ets> to feast luxuriously. See <er>Dominate</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To rule with insolence or arbitrary sway;
to play the master; to be overbearing; to tyrannize; to bluster; to
swell with conscious superiority or haughtiness; -- often with
<xex>over</xex>; <as>as, to <ex>domineer</ex> over
dependents</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go to the feast, revel and <qex>domineer</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His wishes tend abroad to roam,⟦br⟧
And hers to <qex>domineer</qex> at home.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Domineering</ent>⟦br⟧
